OL,7,FThere are also criticisms that when
OL,8,FBlack History is opted to be taught in
OL,9,Fschools, it is only through the narrow
OL,10,Fperspective of triumph over adversity.
OL,11,FInforming students of Britain's role
OL,12,Fin the transatlantic slave trade,
OL,13,Ffollowed by outlawing it. Or the civil
OL,14,Frights movement in the United States.
OL,16,FThe overall impact of colonialism and
OL,17,Fthe British Empire is often overlooked
OL,18,Fand restricted to within higher
OL,19,Feducation settings.
